AB  - Estimates of real output, real input, and total factor productivity are constructed for South Korea for the period 1960–1973. The average annual growth rates are 9.7%, 5.5%, and 41% respectively, higher than the major developed countries. Also, capital deepening is observed to contribute substantially less to growth in Korea than elsewhere.
